tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated creatinine (1.4 mg/dL; normal up to 1.3 mg/dL), which may suggest early renal impairment or dehydration. HbA1c is at the upper limit of normal (6.0%), indicating possible impaired glucose tolerance. Other parameters, including electrolytes, blood count, and platelets, are unremarkable. Recommend clinical correlation and, if indicated, follow-up of renal function and glycemic status.
